France Wants Tax Deal With Liechtenstein, Handelszeitung Says

-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l
-- 
2011-05-26T09:10:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/france-wants-tax-deal-with-liechtenstein-handelszeitung-says.html
France  is holding informal talks with
Liechtenstein on a voluntary disclosure agreement for undeclared
assets similar to the one the principality has with the U.K.,
Handelszeitung reported, citing unidentified people close to
government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carolyn Bandel in Zurich at 
 cbandel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  